 Escríbame a (Mathias "AmiDog" Roslund): fpse.emu@amidog.se

@endnode

@node "history" "Historia"

 Novedades en la versión 0.10.4:

 * Generic:
   - Made plugins aware of link mode status.
 * FPSE:
   - Fixed MUI version tag.
   - Some layout/menu changes to make it more user friendly.
   - Added experimental anti blanker support (fakes key release).
 * fpse.dll:
   - Fixed possible crash in link mode if using BIOS emulation.
 * gpuw3d.dll:
   - Fixed bug preventing the plugin from working with software renderers (Wazp3D).
   - Ported to AROS.
   - Improved link mode support.
 * gpupeops.dll:
   - Improved link mode support.
 * joykey.dll:
   - Improved link mode support.


 New in 0.10.3:

 * FPSE:
   - The FPSE icon is now used as AppIcon when iconifying the GUI.
 * fpse.dll:
   - Linkmode should now work on M680x0 and x86 as well.
 * gpuw3d.dll:
   - Alpha threshold can now be changed using a slider (0-100 gives 0.00 to 1.00).
 * joyll.dll
   - New. Joypad emulation using lowlevel.library + keyboard.


 New in 0.10.2:

 * Generic:
   - Ported to MorphOS (PPC) and AROS (x86). AROS port still has various issues.
 * joypsx.dll:
   - The Port configuration option was always ignored. Fixed.


 New in 0.10.1:

 * Generic:
   - Completely new DLL system which is smaller and better suited for FPSE's needs.
 * FPSE:
   - Fixed null pointer access in the tooltype parser.
 * gpupeops.dll:
   - Removed some unused code and replaced some floating point math with integer one.
   - Added fallback handling in case bitmap locking fails.
   - Various changes in an atempt to work around the M68k FPU flag issues in MorphOS.
   - Fixed the bug which made the screenmode requester crash in the OS3 version.
 * gpuw3d.dll:
   - Fixed the bug which made the screenmode requester crash in the OS3 version.


 New in 0.10.0:

 * Generic:
   - New plugin format with proper version handling.
   - Improved the about information for all the plugins.
   - OS3 M680x0 version, optimized for 68060, ColdFire friendly recompiler.
 * FPSE:
   - The memory cards can now be selected, usefull if you have many.
   - New options: "Optimized engines", "External MDEC", "CDDA to SPU", "SPU Sync".
   - New gamelist editor, nothing fancy, but working.
 * fpse.dll:
   - Based on the much faster and more compatible 0.10 FPSE core.
     . New optimized recompiler with both static and dynamic register cache.
     . SUBQ (subchannel) emulation makes more games work.
     . BIOS emulation, many games can now be played without a BIOS file.
     . Static recompiler, will replace commonly used PSX functions with fast native
       ones. Only used when BIOS emulation is enabled.
     . The PSX startup logo can now be disabled for faster booting.
   - Altivec optimized MDEC playback (if Altivec is present).
   - F8 is used as an eject button and allows the CD to be changed.
   - Converted to plugin (dll) format instead of being a CLI application.
   - Link mode support, works with Destruction Derby among others.
   - Can now read CDDA using the CD plugin and feed it to the SPU plugin.
   - New gamelist system for game specific fixes and optimizations.
   - New SPU Sync feature for synchronous SPU processing and higher compatibility.
 * spupeops.dll:
   - Fixed endian bugs breaking audio playback in the mad1st demo for example.
   - New AHI code which implements a single virtual FIFO buffer. This allows much
     less audio to be emulated each time which will make emulation smoother (as less
     CPU is used each time) and probably improve audio in timing critical games.
   - Fixed XA playback bug causing stuttering/clicks and generally bad audio.
   - Will now return an error to FPSE in case AHI can't be opened.
 * cdimage.dll:
   - Properly handles disk changes and canceled filerequester at startup.
   - Much improved status handling (CD present, tray open, etc).
   - CDDA playback (optional). Requires DATA + TOC file pair (see below).
   - Support for various image formats:
     . DATA: BIN, IMG, RAW, ISO, MDF
     . SUBQ: SBI, SUB, MDF
     . TOC : CUE, CCD
 * cdrom.dll:
   - Properly handles disk changes and no CD present at startup.
   - Much improved status handling (CD present, tray open, etc).
   - CDDA playback.
   - CD reading speed can be reduced to 2X (if the drive supports it).
   - Fixed subchannel handling when changing CD's.
   - The read mode autodetecting wasn't really working, fixed.
 * gpuw3d.dll:
   - Warp3D plugin. Bugfixed version of the old OS3.x WOS one. Still has many bugs.
   - Options to hide the mouse pointer and turn speed limit on and off.
   - Support for the PSX GPU texture window feature.
   - Options to select texture reduction and number of textures to cache.
   - Completely rewritten using gpupeops as foundation, much better.
   - Will now show images viewed using DMA from PSX mem to VRAM.
   - Now use multitexturing to be able to properly render textures the PSX way.
   - Experimental support for scaled rendering, will not work with all games.
   - Support for the PSX ability to control semitransparency on a per-pixel basis.
   - The Warp3D context wasn't destroyed on exit (=major memory leak), fixed.
 * joymouse.dll:
   - Will now capture all used mouse events making it usefull even in window mode.
 * joykey.dll:
   - Now displays the keys names rather than the non-userfriendly rawkey numbers.
   - Emulation of dual shock analog controller.
 * gpupete.dll:
   - If the screenmode requester is canceled, it will now default to window.
   - Support for custom window size and fullscreen mode with preselected resolution.
   - Options to hide the mouse pointer and turn speed limit on and off.
   - Obsolete (removed, no longer supported).
 * joyai:
   - New. Joypad emulation using AmigaInput + keyboard.
   - Analog sticks (AXIS) can be used to emulate digital directional pads (D-PAD).
 * gpupeops.dll:
   - New. Ported P.E.Op.S. GPU plugin based on my gpupete port.
   - Faster and, in some cases, much faster than the old gpupete.
   - Support for the P.E.Op.S. postprocessing filters. Very CPU intensive.
 * spuwave.dll:
   - New. A simple SPU plugin. Doesn't support reverb, interpolation, etc, but is
fast.
 * spuxa.dll:
   - New. A modified null plugin which *only* can play XA/CDDA audio.
 * joymtap.dll:
   - New. Multitap plugin. Allows up to 8 players in some games.
 * joygun.dll:
   - New. Emulation of Namco gun using Amiga mouse.
 * joypsx.dll:
   - New. Emulation of PSX pad using the PSX Port adapter.

@endnode

